# Cloudflare Workers static-assets custom headers (issue #47).
#
# Vite copies public/ into dist/, so this file ships with the build and the
# Worker applies these rules to every asset response. This is the real-header
# home of the Content-Security-Policy that index.html also carries as a <meta>
# tag — real headers can additionally carry `frame-ancestors 'none'` (a
# clickjacking defence the <meta> CSP cannot express).
#
# style-src keeps 'unsafe-inline': framer-motion writes per-frame inline
# transform/opacity styles and several components set dynamic style={{…}}
# (meters, gradients, evidence threads) that can't be hash/nonce-pinned. All
# other directives stay locked to 'self'; script-src has NO 'unsafe-inline'.
/*
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data:; media-src 'self'; font-src 'self'; connect-src 'self'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'none'; frame-ancestors 'none'
